<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Customize Moving Average Model</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-latest.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/3.5.6/d3.min.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Customize Moving Average Model for {{ticker}}</h1>

    <p>
      Customize your {{ticker}} moving average model by changing the window of
      days considered while calculating the moving average. Read more about
      moving averages <a>here</a>.
    </p>

    <form action="/ma/customize" method="POST">
      <label
        >Enter the number of days you want in your moving average window
        here</label
      >
      <input type="number" placeholder="Ex. - 277" name="window" />
      <input type="hidden" name="ticker" value="{{ticker}}" />
      <input type="submit" />
    </form>

    <div class="chart" id="plot_ma">
      <script>
        var graphs = {{moving_average_plot | safe}};

        Plotly.plot("plot_ma", graphs, {});
      </script>
    </div>

    <p>Current moving average window - {{window}}</p>
  </body>
</html>
